   {:e #blake3 "156fe9491cb50f8518b8f0fecd6bbb42d534a37c880369b44afd8f49bb6d5ffa" :a :db/ident :v :harvest/session-braid-user-1774296934 :op :assert}
   {:e #blake3 "156fe9491cb50f8518b8f0fecd6bbb42d534a37c880369b44afd8f49bb6d5ffa" :a :harvest/accomplishments :v "WHY THIS CLOSES THE LOOP: The dog-food showed braid is a 'capture tool not discovery tool' because the acquisition function only scored EXISTING items. Bridge hypothesis generation makes it a DISCOVERY tool: it reads the knowledge graph structure, identifies where connections are missing (free energy is high), proposes hypothetical bridging observations, scores them against the SAME F(S) metric, and surfaces the top bridge as a QUESTION alongside task recommendations. The agent then explores (answers the question), the outcome is measured (actual ΔF(S) vs predicted), the lifecycle attributes calibrate (Bayesian weight adjusts), and the next round of bridge hypotheses is more accurate. The system learns to ask better questions by measuring the value of its previous questions. This is the hypothetico-deductive method applied to the exploration process itself.; Session entity: :task/t-136cbef9; Session entity: :recon/trace-5a3485d367be2d2c; Session entity: :task/t-f7b80ea7; DOG-FOOD GO CLI (Agent 2 Exploration): Usefulness 4/10, Guidance Quality 3/10, Observation UX 5/10, Knowledge Persistence 6/10, C8 5/10. Key insight: braid is a knowledge CAPTURE tool not a DISCOVERY tool. M(t) stayed at 0.55 entire session (uninformative). F(S) barely moved 0.52->0.56. Seed leaks braid's own codebase info (115K LOC Rust, cargo commands) into Go project context. Highest value: harvest urgency reminders, task ready prioritization, COTX auto-task.; Session entity: :task/t-e9471f3a; Session entity: :recon/trace-9504bf2f389e1bb4; Session entity: :task/t-eae39095; Session entity: :session/s-1774296350; Session entity: :task/t-06ba2f20; Session entity: :task/t-5da9064a; THE SYNTHESIS — FREE ENERGY GRADIENT + CONNECTION LIFECYCLE (ADR-029 + ADR-030): The acquisition function proposes EDGES (ADR-029). project_delta scores those edges by E[ΔF(S)] (the free energy gradient). The six :attention/* attributes track each edge's lifecycle: birth (hypothesis generated) → activation (presented to agent) → Hebbian strengthening (agent follows up) → Bayesian calibration (outcome measured) → decay (novelty decreases) → death (retracted if falsified). Bridge hypotheses between weakly-connected knowledge communities ARE connection entities with the full lifecycle schema. generate_bridge_hypotheses() creates them, project_delta scores them, the hypothesis ledger calibrates them. ONE mechanism (ΔF(S) over hypotheticals) + ONE schema (6 lifecycle attributes) + ONE calibration pipeline (hypothesis ledger) = complete active inference. No separate exploration/creativity parameters needed — they emerge from the F(S) landscape.; Session entity: :task/t-06215eb2; Session entity: :recon/trace-c407d502d96e63ac; Session entity: :task/t-5c8eab95; ACP AUDIT: 16/24 commands use ActionProjection. 8 legacy commands (init, verify, challenge, extract, wrap, config, write subactions) still use footer injection. 96 context blocks across 15 files have attention:None — no UAQ scoring. Presentation tracking only in status command. compute_calibration_metrics called 2x per command (routing.rs + context.rs), no caching. Novelty formula 1/sqrt(N) duplicated in 3 places. record_block_presentations missing retraction datoms for old counts.; Session entity: :task/t-65edfa1a; Session entity: :task/t-238ea707; Session entity: :recon/trace-901e3dc153cd05a2; POPPERIAN EXPLORATION: Every exploration hypothesis is falsifiable at three levels: (1) INFORMATION falsification — explored X, learned nothing new (IG≈0). (2) RELEVANCE falsification — learned something but it doesn't connect to goals (pragmatic value≈0). (3) MAGNITUDE falsification — learned less than predicted (|predicted_IG - actual_IG| > threshold). Each mode teaches something different: (1) coverage model overestimated fog, (2) relevance model misjudged connection to goals, (3) IG estimator miscalibrated. The comonadic depth ladder applies: OPINION(depth 0, gap detected)→HYPOTHESIS(depth 1, prediction registered with falsification)→TESTED(depth 2, outcome measured)→SURVIVED(depth 3, not falsified)→KNOWLEDGE(depth 4, promoted to transferable exploration heuristic). Depth 4 = learning to learn.; Session entity: :recon/trace-c0a4f0146b0d114d; Session entity: :task/t-8dcb3939; Session entity: :task/t-78f32d55; Session entity: :task/t-f843f44c; Session entity: :task/t-3d5e9546; EPISTEMOLOGICAL SLAM: Braid does Simultaneous Localization And Mapping for knowledge. The agent simultaneously: (1) LOCALIZES — what do I know? what's my epistemic state? (the seed), (2) MAPS — what does the knowledge space look like? what regions exist? (observations → coverage model), (3) PLANS — where should I explore next? what's behind the fog? (the free energy gradient). The knowledge map and the exploration strategy are co-dependent. The map grows its own frontier — every observation reveals new questions. The comonadic duplicate of the store IS the exploration graph. ADR-029 says connections are datoms with lifecycle attributes. ADR-030 says score those connections by projected ΔF(S).; Session entity: :task/t-00c2f4b2; Session entity: :recon/trace-a1087108cc5ea442; Session entity: :task/t-d3e784b8; Session entity: :recon/trace-9e1b5cab5f5f62b8; Session entity: :task/t-0988fa40; Session entity: :recon/trace-1ae004adaa0e85c6; LÉVY FLIGHT CREATIVITY: The comonadic projection is LOCAL — only sees the neighborhood. The most valuable discoveries are often NON-LOCAL (distant connections, cross-domain analogies). Optimal foraging theory shows Lévy flights (heavy-tailed random walks) are optimal for patchy resource landscapes. Knowledge IS patchy. The creativity temperature τ controls exploration range: τ≈0 (focused, comonadic neighborhood), τ≈0.5 (associative, cross-store semantic similarity), τ≈1.0 (analogical, training data patterns). BUT under the free energy formulation, τ emerges naturally: when local observations have low projected ΔF(S), only distant bridges have high gradient, so the system naturally makes long-range jumps. No separate parameter needed IF project_delta is computed over hypotheticals at multiple scales.; Session entity: :task/t-a6768e84; Session entity: :task/t-8df51232; Session entity: :task/t-ad7974fd; Session entity: :task/t-88ca2bbf; Session entity: :task/t-0210660b; DOG-FOOD SPEC PROJECT (Agent 3 C8): C8 Score 5/10. TWO CRITICAL VIOLATIONS: (1) harvest codebase-snapshot captures braid's own 115K LOC Rust, not the target YAML project — walks up to parent directory. (2) harvest git-summary captures braid's git history, not target project. HIGH: braid trace hardcoded for Rust comments. MEDIUM: seed injects cargo/braid API patterns into non-Rust project. MEDIUM: M(t) spec-lang penalizes external spec formats. WORKED: observe/task/spec-create/bilateral/challenge/witness all domain-agnostic.; Session entity: :task/t-f71d4be3; DOG-FOOD GO CLI (Agent 1 Lifecycle): 9/9 steps PASS. F(S) 0.51->0.56. 8 bugs found: --verbose=bare duplicate, --json outputs text not JSON, --datoms flag ignored, extractors fail on recursive self-invoke, git=no in monorepo, init rejects positional arg, harvest auto-task titles overflow 600+ chars, cargo detected in Go project. Core lifecycle (init->observe->task->harvest->seed) fully functional on 62.5K LOC Go project. External readiness 7/10.; Session entity: :task/t-263d4afd\nSession entity: :task/t-a13782e8; Gradient Universality — all items scored by E[ΔF(S)] / cost; Bridge Generation from Graph Structure — hypotheticals traceable to spectral partition; Session entity: :task/t-e656e270; The Free Energy Gradient — hypothetical observation scoring via project_delta over bridge hypotheses; Session entity: :task/t-7007ba04; Gradient Self-Calibration — projected vs actual ΔF(S) error decreases" :op :assert}
